title: Thousands attend pro-Palestine rallies across Australia as organisers vow to keep protesting after Gaza ceasefire
summary: Sydney organizers pledge to persist in their protests for a free Palestine, emphasizing their commitment to the cause. Meanwhile, others express optimism that a US-brokered deal could lead to an end to the conflict and alleviate suffering. The juxtaposition highlights the ongoing tension between activism and diplomatic efforts in addressing the situation.
